Have you said or thought any of those lately? If so, you might have an alligator or two you\'92re feeding. \
\
Every one of those statements speak to the size of the issue, not to the seriousness if it were to get out of hand. If it were to bite you back. And that\'92s why we continue to feed things we know are bad for us. We look it the size. It\'92s small, cute, maybe even cuddly and we can\'92t ever imagine it growing up. \
\
So let me ask again..what are you feeding that isn't hurting you but may one day get out of hand if you don't quit feeding it?\
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs34 \cf2 WHAT YOU FEED GROWS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs30 \cf2 \
We bought a new puppy a week ago. She was 8 weeks old when we got and her. She\'92s a small black and white boxer weighing on a few pounds and we love her. But every single day we feed it, multiple times a day in fact. And already, she\'92s getting bigger. And in a few months we will not have a nine pound puppy but a 85 pound full grown boxer. Right now, I can control her, but in a few months she\'92ll be able to drag me across the yard if she wants. \
\
Why? Because what you feed grows. (no one probably highlighted that last sentence because it's so obvious). \
\

\f1\b But what's obvious many times is ignored. 
\f0\b0 In fact that's the whole point of the book. I'm pretty sure nothing I'm going to say is going to point out any new sin you've never thought about. The point is to shed light back onto the things we tend to ignore because they are so obvious.
\f1\b \

\f0\b0 \
You see, it doesn\'92t matter what IT is. If you feed IT, IT will grow...and grow...and grow. Until IT is bigger than you. Until you can no longer control IT. Until it drags you across the lawn, into divorce court, into debt, into a medical issue, into ruined relationships, into depression, into anxiety, into bitterness, or into overwhelming addiction you can no longer hide.\
\
What we feed grows, and it's only a matter of time before what you feed will get a hold of you and your life is forever changed because of it.\'a0 \
\
Whatever you do with this book, whether you finish it or not, DON'T FEED THE ALLIGATORS.\
\
